    </div><!-- /p-8 -->
  </div><!-- /card -->

  <div class="mt-6 w-full max-w-lg text-xs text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 space-y-1 text-center">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Progress is saved automatically.</strong>
      Non-sensitive form fields (connection details, company info, username) are stored in your
      browser&rsquo;s <code class="font-mono">localStorage</code> and in a server-side
      <code class="font-mono">config/wizard-draft.json</code> file after each step.
      Passwords are never stored in either location.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you return after a browser restart, <code class="font-mono">localStorage</code> is used first;
      if that&rsquo;s empty, the server draft is used as a fallback.
      Both are deleted permanently when setup completes.
    </p>
    <p class="pt-1">
      The final configuration is written to <code class="font-mono">config/app-config.json</code>.
      Environment variables always take priority over this file.
    </p>
    <p class="pt-2">
      <button type="button" onclick="clearWizardDraft()"
        class="text-red-400 dark:text-red-500 hover:underline hover:text-red-600 dark:hover:text-red-400 transition">
        Clear saved progress
      </button>
      — removes browser localStorage and asks the server to delete its draft too.
    </p>
  </div>

  <script>
  function clearWizardDraft() {
    ['hcs_setup_step1','hcs_setup_step2','hcs_setup_step3'].forEach(k => localStorage.removeItem(k));
    fetch('/setup/clear-draft', { method: 'POST' }).finally(() => location.reload());
  }
  </script>

</body>
</html>
